The paper discusses the design of medium access control protocols for cognitive radios, which involves the use of information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also deals with cognitive radios, which fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of a sequential design approach and the development of an asymptotically optimal strategy suggest the involvement of control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of efficient medium access strategies, which could involve machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category as well.
